    "John Trapp": "The first wherein was, &amp;c. ] He speaks nothing of the outer court, as not pertinent to his present purpose. But there was both in the tabernacle and temple, the holy of holies, the sanctuary, and the court of the people: answerable whereunto are in man, \"The spirit, soul, and body,\" #1Th 5:23 . And as the cloud, #1Ki 8:10,11 , filled first the most holy place, and then the holy, and then the outer court, so doth the Holy Ghost renew the spirit of our minds, and then our wills and affections, and then the outward man.\nVer.\n2. The first wherein was, &c.] He speaks nothing of the outer court, as not pertinent to his present purpose. But there was both in the tabernacle and temple, the holy of holies, the sanctuary, and the court of the people: answerable whereunto are in man, \"The spirit, soul, and body,\" #1Th 5:"
